<h2>Specific climate indicators for April 2018</h2>
April was characterized by high temperatures in large parts of Central Europe, with high anomalies in average, maximum and minimum temperatures (see the following section).
Figure 2 shows the amount of frost days and the anomaly for April 2018. Especially the alpine regions and the southern part of Sweden show a large anomaly with much less frost days than normal, resulting in rapid snowmelt.
<br><br>
<br><br>
