<h2>The weather in April 2018</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
In April 2018 daily average and maximum temperatures were much above average over almost all of Central- and Eastern Europe and in many parts even exceptionally above average. In these areas also daily minimum temperatures were (much) above average. In the UK and Scandinavia daily average and maximum temperatures were near average. In the central and northern sections of Sweden even slightly below minimum temperatures were measured mainly due to good radiation conditions during the nights in polar air under high pressure.
